            <step1>
                <para count="1">If voltages
                    <emph type="bold">are not</emph>
                    within limits, a faulty sensor, connector or wiring harness is indicated and further testing is
                    required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the voltages are within limits, the pyrometer gauge should be checked for a sticky
                    needle (refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s08313_HL0831302.xml" xrefid="hl0831305">Restricted Needle Movement</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">The needle sticks, replace the pyrometer gauge.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">The needle moves freely, check internal voltage.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Internal Voltage Check</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn key switch to OFF, remove the pyrometer gauge from cluster and make sure the
                    cluster harness connectors are properly installed on the cluster (refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s08313_HL0831303.xml" xrefid="hl0831303">CLUSTER HARNESS CONNECTORS</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the key switch to ACC and measure the voltage across the gauge's cluster socket
                    pins. Refer to GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL, Circuit Diagrams. Pyrometer reference voltage is at Terminal
                    1, Sensor voltage at Terminal 3 and Ground at Terminal 2.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the proper voltages
                        <emph type="bold">are not</emph>
                        present, replace cluster with a new gaugeless cluster and re-install gauges.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the voltages are correct, turn the key switch to OFF and re-install the pyrometer
                        gauge. Turn the key switch to ACC and if the gauge
                        <emph type="bold">does not</emph>
                        operate, replace the gauge.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
